From: mdm@cis.ohio-state.edu (Michael Moore)
Subject: TkWWW - port to LINUX with TERM support
Date: 22 Aug 1993 01:28:41 -0400

        Hello,

        This is to ask if anyone is interested in a port of tkWWW
to linux.  I will be happy to provide it to anyone who might find
it useful, just drop me a line.  If enough people ask for it,
I'll try and get it on sunsite or somesuch.

        TkWWW is the Tcl/Tk World Wide Web browser for X windows.  For
those who don't know yet, Tcl/Tk is a free motifish looking toolkit
for X.  It now comes as part of the SLS distribution.

        I ported it because I didn't find it out on the net and
I really wanted to have WWW access from home, but with a nice
interface.    Xmosaic seemed to need Motif, which I don't have, 
so I went for the next best thing.

        The program uses "term" to provide the necessary access
to the internet, if necessary.

        Sincerely,

        Michael Moore
        (mdm@cis.ohio-state.edu)

